{
  "id": "momentum_trend_strategy_001",
  "name": "Composite Momentum Trend Strategy",
  "description": "This strategy employs a composite directional impulse filter to identify momentum trends in daily price bars. It triggers entries based on a 14-day Rolling Hurst Exponent exceeding 0.55 and a price close above the upper band of a 20-day Keltner Channel, confirming breakout signals with volume analysis.",
  "algorithm_type": "Momentum",
  "prompt": "I want to create a trend momentum strategy that trades on daily bars using a composite directional impulse filter combined with volume-driven breakout confirmation. Entry triggers when the 14-day Rolling Hurst Exponent rises above 0.55, indicating directional persistence, AND the price closes above the upper band of a 20-day Keltner Channel calculated on typical price (average of high, low, close). Simultaneously, the volume on the entry day must exceed the 10-day average volume by at least 25%, confirming breakout conviction. Exit occurs when the price closes below the lower 10-day exponential moving average of the close price OR when the 14-day Rolling Hurst Exponent falls below 0.45, signaling loss of trend strength. Stop-loss is set at 1.5 times the 14-day Average True Range below the entry price. This strategy uniquely combines Hurst-based trend persistence filtering with volume-validated channel breakouts for selective trend entries and momentum confirmation.",
